entries.dooku_datadisk_01: Padawan - The data disk tells the story of Dooku's youth and training in the Jedi Order. Born from nobility, the young Dooku was trained as a Jedi from an early age. During his years as a padawan he trained under some of the greatest Jedi of his time.
entries.dooku_datadisk_02: Jedi Master - The data disk describes Dooku's promotion to Jedi Knight and the training of padawan of his own, including Qui-Gon Jinn. Dooku was granted the rank of Jedi Master with Qui-Gon Jinn's successful passage from Padawan to Jedi Knight.
entries.dooku_datadisk_03: Leaving the Order - The data disk tells of Dooku and his loss of faith in the Republic and the Jedi Order. Shortly after the Battle of Naboo and the death of his former student, Qui-Gon Jinn, Dooku formally left the Jedi Order.
entries.dooku_datadisk_04: Embracing the Dark Side - The data disk contains the story of how Dooku assumed his inherited title of Count and rose to be one of the leaders of the Separatists' Movement prior to the outbreak of the Clone War.
entries.dooku_datadisk_05: Dooku's Death - On the final data disk, the last years of Count Dooku's life are recorded. Here, many of his actions during the Clone War are told. The story ends with his death, at the hands of Anakin Skywalker, during the Battle of Coruscant.

entries.camera_01: You have found a camera left behind in the dirt. The last pictures stored shows confused pictures of people running from an unseen threat.
entries.datadisk_letter_01: You have found a datadisk containing a letter from an employee at the nearby research. The letter is addressed to his family.
entries.broken_rifle_01: You have found a broken and battered rifle. It hints at the violent events that took place here.
entries.torn_shirt_01: You have found a torn and bloody shirt.
entries.stuffed_bantha_01: You have found a dirty stuffed bantha found on the ground at Camp Alpha. There was no sign of the previous owner.
entries.signal_flare_01: You have found a signal flare, it looks like it was already used.
entries.bloody_knife_01: You have found a bloody knife. It was clearly used in a fight recently.
entries.cracked_helmet_01: You have found a cracked and damaged helmet. Judging by the damage to the helm you doubt that the person wearing the helm survived the fight.
entries.movement_sensor_01: You have found a handheld movement sensor.
entries.radio_antenna_01: You have found a radio antenna, used for long range emergency broadcasts.
entries.bracelet_01: You have found a bracelet found on the ground. There's no sight of the pervious owner.
entries.pistol_01: You have found a damaged pistol. It looks like the damaged was caused by overheating.
entries.id_card_01: You have found an ID card belonging to a research assistant. When looking closer you can see small stains of blood on the card.
entries.survival_kit: You have found a survival kit containing a number of useful items for anyone stranded in the wilderness.
entries.flash_light_01: You have found a flash light. It looks like the energy cell is depleted.
entries.batteries_01: You have found a set of batteries, useable in a wide range of portable electronic devices.
entries.broken_radio_01: You have found a broken radio. It looks like it was hit several times with a blunt object.
entries.medical_kit_01: You have found a medical kit. It looks most of the supplies inside have been used already.
entries.emergency_rations_01: You have found a box of emergency rations.
entries.cracked_storm_armor_01: You have found a cracked stormtrooper chestplate. The area around the fracture are covered in dried blood.
entries.unused_shuttle_ticket_01: You have found an unused shuttle ticket. It looks like someone had hoped to make it off the planet. However it doesen't look like the previous owner made it.
entries.radar_beacon_01: You have found a radar beacon. It's still active, sending out a signal requesting immediate assistance from anyone hearing the signal.
entries.datadisk_diary_01: You have found a datadisk diary. The last entry tells of the confused attempts to get to a shuttle just to find that it had already left by the time the author reached the launch site.
entries.bloody_jacket_01: You have found a bloody jacket with several wide gaps torn accross the back.
entries.holo_recording_rod_01: You have found a device used for holo recordings. The only thing you can hear recorded on this device is a strange hissing sound.
entries.used_med_kit_01: You have found a used medical kit with a number of bandages missing.
entries.depleted_energy_cartridge_01: You have found a depleted energy cartridge of a type used in some older blasters
entries.cargo_pockets_01: You have found a pair of cargo pockets used to carry tools and supplies.
entries.cooking_utensils_01: You have found a set of cooking utensils.
entries.ambush_detector_01: You have found a deviced used to detect lifesigns in an area, with the goal of detecting a potential ambush before it's too late.
entries.scout_pistol_01: You have found a small scout pistol.
entries.basket_01: You have found a basket containing a number of personal items. The owner is nowhere to be found.
entries.pet_cage_01: You have found a small cage used to hold or transport house pets. This one appears to be empty.
entries.dmg_vibro_sword_01: You have found a damaged vibro sword.
entries.ammo_canister_01: You have found a canister containing ammunition for explosive weapons.
entries.camping_cot_01: You have found a portable cot, often used while camping.
entries.signal_scanner_01: You have found a signal scanner used to scan a wide range of frequencies for radio signals.
entries.power_converter_01: You have found a power converter used in various forms of machinery.
entries.medical_scanner_01: You have found a device used to scan patients for internal damage.
entries.holodisk_01: You have found a blank holodisk.
entries.backpack_01: You have found a packpack with various personal items.
entries.computer_toolkit_01: You have found a toolkit used to maintain and repair computer terminals.
entries.medical_console_01: You have found a medical console used by medics in the diagosis and treatment of patients.
entries.used_antidote_kit_01: You have found a used antidote kit.
entries.medical_analysis_tool_01: You have found an analysis tool used in locating and identifying infections in patients.
entries.carbine_01: You have found a carbine with a depleted energy clip.
entries.locator_beacon_01: You have found a locator beacon, used in signaling your location to space ships in planetary orbit.
entries.radio_01: You have found a broken short range radio
entries.camp_fire_01: You have found a smoldering campfire. There is no sign of the people who started it.
entries.cracked_datapad_01: You have found a datapad with a large crack in the display. It does not appear to working.
